Now & Then
#letyourvoicebeheard… always

Dreams collide 💭 I moved to LA in hopes of teaching and reaching new heights as a dance/creator. Blessedly, I’ve been able to travel, work with major artists and teach master classes all over the Americas, with classes up to 500 students. More recently, I’ve been songwriting, producing, mixing music for choreographers/artists and it’s a passion I’m falling deeply in love with just as I did with dance. So now… creating the music I teach to has been a beautiful collision of passions coming at just the right time. Thank you @ndadance for having me this week! I’m looking forward to continued teaching & producing for you. Thank you students for receiving the knowledge and growing so tremendously in front of my eyes. And big thanks to my assistants and head instructors @yim.anna @_morgan.ann__ @coltonheier0628 for running an awesome camp! P.S. If any teams want mixes from class or customs remixes. Check my bio link! I’m a wizard 🧙🏽‍♂️ and I’d love to share the magic! More to come 🖤💙 #wegotthis #markusshieldschoreography #theworkisworthit #NDADANCE #DANCE #chingy #thronesunknown

One time for the Lou! 🐔🔥🐔🔥🐔 Second master class this week was amazing. Thank you @NDADANCE for allowing me to contribute to these amazing kids! Grateful grateful! #markusshieldschoreography #ndadance #chingy #rightthurr
